26/08/2003
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- Russian oil giant Lukoil was chosen on Monday (25 August) as the buyer of an 80 per cent stake in Serbia's second-largest oil products distributor.
Beopetrol owns more than 180 petrol stations and seven warehouses, and employs 1,650 people.
It controls about 17 per cent of Serbia's market for oil products.
Lukoil will pay 117m euros in cash and has promised to invest another 85m in Beopetrol over the next five years.
(AP - 25/08/03)
